title: Middletown: A Study in American Culture (Lynd, 1929) [PDF]
description: Middletown: A Study in Modern American Culture (1929) Written by Robert Staughton Lynd & Helen Merrell Lynd PDF Scan of 1956 Edition - DRM Stripped https://openlibrary.org/books/OL23263959M/Middletown The first of two classic studies that examined the daily life of a typical small american city-in actuality, Muncie, Indiana-in the mid-1920s, using the approach of social anthropology. Of enduring interest to students of SOCIOLOGY (740), these works inspired an acclaimed six-part television series.
